This chunk is part of the C++ implementation example in the document, specifically showing how to set up the camera position and initialize the simulation task. It occurs after loading and positioning the models (cube and smiley) and before entering the simulation loop that handles physics calculations and updates.

// Set the camera position
  camera.set_pos(80, -20, 40);
  camera.look_at(0, 0, 0);

  PT(GenericAsyncTask) simulationTaskObject =
    new GenericAsyncTask("startup task", &simulationTask, nullptr);
  simulationTaskObject->set_delay(2);
  taskMgr->add(simulationTaskObject);
}
